<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38221d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38221d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38221d"> 221(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> search competence / love unity / knowledge stupefaction / altruism</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So in the Mantak of al-Tayr (Colloquy of the Flyers) the Birds, emblems of souls, seeking the presence of the gigantic feathered biped Simurgh, their god, traverse seven Seas (according to other seven Wadys) <mark>of Search, of Love, of Knowledge, of Competence, of Unity, of Stupefaction, and of Altruism</mark> (<i>i.e.</i> annihilation of self), the several stages of contemplative life. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 130</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: <cite>FW</cite> 604.29 derives from <a name="n56123a" href="n56all.htm#n56123a">N56 (VI.B.41):123(a)</a>.</mm> </dd></dl>
